data.title: Leadership Projects - Nisonger Center - The Ohio State University
data.snippet:
Aspirations is a group-based weekly social skills program at the Nisonger Center for adolescents and young adults (aged 15-30 years) with Autism Spectrum Disorder. While the Aspirations participants are meeting, their caregiver(s) are invited to participate in a weekly informational support group, the Aspirations Caregiver Group. The group offers resources and support to caregivers navigating the participantâ€™s transition from adolescence into adulthood. Trainees involved in this leadership project created a manual for future leaders of the caregiver group using universal design principles. Two versions of the manual were created (physical and digital) to increase accessibility and usability among current caregiver group facilitators. Trainees frequently met with group facilitators to [...] Trainees frequently met with group facilitators to discuss manual contents and to test out manual instructions to ensure a clear understanding of current facilitators. The manual will be used and edited as needed for future facilitators of the Aspirations Caregiver Group.
